snippet.textDisplay:
Ao happy to finally see a new Sindhi song from Coke Studio Pakistan, we are originally from Sindh, my grandparents shitfted to India when they were very young, have heard stories from them, happy to see it reflect via this song.

We have heard of Sindh but never been there, not sure when we get to visit but this song feels like a peek into the culture, music, and art of Sindh and for that, thank you. ❤

snippet.textDisplay: Peacock is the traditional bird of Tharparkar Sindh. Dolphins are found in Indus River, Sindh. This song celebrates the arrival and bravery of Marvi who was abducted by the King Umar of that time. Due to her resistance, he released her after few years. Peacock represents the arrival of Marvi in this song.

snippet.textDisplay: That peacock and dolphin actually representing, a loud massage and awareness for the protection of indigenous animals of sindh, blind dolphin is a symbolic animal of Indus River, which is now at the verge of extinction.
